  "body": "### TODO\r\n\r\nActivity UX:\r\n\r\n- The user should see the entry in activity as `dapp`\r\n- The user should see the sign method of WalletConnect\r\n\r\n#### Technical requirements\r\n\r\nFor `session_request` of send transactions\r\n\r\n- [ ] Add to `multi_transactions` table\r\n- [ ] Track transaction a to trigger downloader and link for activity entry\r\n- [ ] Register sign as WalletConnect\r\n- [ ] Link with dapp list\r\n\r\n### History\r\n\r\nFrom Ben:\r\n\r\n\"... it would work like the transactions we currently have in the wallet activity flows for wallet interactions with 3rd party (external) exchanges:\r\n\r\nEg:\r\nhttps://www.figma.com/file/FkFClTCYKf83RJWoifWgoX/Wallet-v2?type=design&node-id=15324-456837&mode=design&t=1jdoSrZs2pptRmus-4\r\n\r\nIn these instances, a buy Tx is shown as a receive Tx (from the exchange/dApp) given that is the end result to the user wallet and a sell Tx is a send Tx (to the exchange/dApp) - again that is the end result to the wallet. \r\n\r\nIn these instances we also show the Tx only when there is 1 confirmation on Mainnet - no pending state. The only difference here is that we could show the Signing method section of the activity detail page because the signing event has been executed on Status desktop.\"",
